BM SETUP UTILITY Inline Documentation - English

Note : Excuse me for my Poor French 2 English Translation


BASIC PRINCIPLES

  To choose a command, move the highlighted Rectangular zone with the
  Up & Down Direction Keys then validate with ENTER or RETURN
  if you modify a setting, you will see the modification in the window
  Informations.

COMMANDS

  I- Select a Sound Card for the digitized sounds (SOUND SETUP)

    Choose NONE if you don't have a Sound Blaster compatible Card,
    else Choose SOUND BLASTER

    Next, you have to indicate the Sound Card Base Address
    (from 210h to 280h). The default option is 220h (please refer to
    your sound card documentation)

    Then choose the DMA Channel used for sound reproduction : 1,2,3 or 4
    (default = 1)

    Then choose the IRQ number : 2,3,5 or 7 (default = 7, sound blaster
    default = 5)


  II- Select a Sound Card for the Musics (MUSIC SETUP)

    Choose NONE if you don't have a Sound Blaster or Adlib compatible
    Sound Card.
    Else Choose ADLIB.

  III- Choose the Mouse Speed (MOUSE SPEED)

    Slow Speed   : LOW
    Medium Speed : MEDIUM (default)
    Fast Speed   : HIGH

  IV- Save your settings & quit the program

      select the SAVE & EXIT command

  V- Quit the program with no change

      Select the EXIT Command


